{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01FqNz4nJR8V27Wh1ZR3uCbQ","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now let me create a comprehensive summary of my findings:\n\n## Summary\n\nI've thoroughly analyzed the Cloche web UI codebase and found all the relevant code related to the \"Project Runs page\" and \"Project Detail page\". Here are the complete findings:\n\n### Web UI File Structure\n\n**Template Files:**\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/layout.html` - Base layout template (533 bytes)\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/projects.html` - Projects listing page (1,297 bytes)\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/runs.html` - Runs listing page (6,585 bytes)\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html` - Run detail page (15,762 bytes)\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html` - **PROJECT DETAIL PAGE** (22,579 bytes)\n\n**Handler & Route Definitions:**\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` - Main handler with all routes (1,853 lines)\n\n**Styling:**\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css` - CSS styling (13,670 bytes)\n\n---\n\n### Route Definitions\n\nThe following routes are defined in `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (lines 147-167):\n\n**HTML Routes:**\n```\nGET /                           → handleProjectOverview    (Projects landing page)\nGET /projects/{name}/runs       → handleProjectRuns        (Project runs page)\nGET /runs                       → handleRunsList           (All runs listing)\nGET /runs/{id}                  → handleRunDetail          (Run detail page)\nGET /projects/{name}            → handleProjectDetail      (Project detail page) ← PROJECT PAGE\nGET /static/*                   → File server\n```\n\n**API Routes:**\n```\nGET /api/projects               → handleAPIProjects\nGET /api/projects/{name}/runs   → handleAPIProjectRuns   (Project runs list API)\nGET /api/runs                   → handleAPIRuns\nGET /api/runs/{id}              → handleAPIRunDetail\nGET /api/runs/{id}/steps/{step}/output → handleAPIStepOutput\nGET /api/runs/{id}/stream       → handleAPIStream        (SSE log streaming)\nPOST /api/runs/{id}/stop        → handleAPIStopRun\nDELETE /api/runs/{id}/container → handleAPIDeleteContainer\nDELETE /api/projects/{name}/containers → handleAPIDeleteProjectContainers\nDELETE /api/containers          → handleAPIDeleteAllContainers\nGET /api/projects/{name}/info   → handleAPIProjectInfo\nGET /api/projects/{name}/info/prompt-diff → handleAPIPromptDiff\nGET /api/projects/{name}/workflows → handleAPIWorkflows\nGET /api/projects/{name}/workflows/{workflow}/steps/{step}/content → handleAPIStepContent\nGET /api/projects/{name}/tasks  → handleAPITasks\n```\n\n---\n\n### Project Detail Page (Project Page)\n\n**Route:** `GET /projects/{name}` (line 151)  \n**Handler:** `handleProjectDetail()` (lines 1199-1233)\n\n**Handler Logic:**\n- Resolves project directory by name/label\n- Lists runs for the project\n- Counts containers for the project\n- Passes data to template: Label, Dir, RecentRuns (dots), ContainerCount\n\n**Template:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html`\n\n**Key Sections in Template:**\n1. **Header** (lines 2): Breadcrumb navigation with project label\n2. **Run History** (lines 4-12): Display recent run status dots with \"View all runs\" button\n3. **Panel 1: Project Info** (lines 14-18): Loads via `/api/projects/{name}/info`\n   - Docker image, version, prompt files with history\n4. **Panel 2: Tasks** (lines 20-24): Loads via `/api/projects/{name}/tasks`\n   - Task pipeline state table\n5. **Panel 3: Workflow View** (lines 26-34): Loads via `/api/projects/{name}/workflows`\n   - Location tabs (Container/Host)\n   - Workflow tabs\n   - DAG visualization with SVG\n6. **Step Drawer** (lines 36-43): Modal for step details\n\n**JavaScript Features:**\n- `loadProjectInfo()`: Fetches project metadata (Docker image, version, prompt files)\n- `toggleDiff()`: Shows/hides git diffs for prompt files\n- `loadWorkflows()`: Builds workflow DAG with step connections\n- `switchLocation()`: Toggles between container and host workflows\n- `showWorkflow()`: Renders Sugiyama-style layout algorithm for graph visualization\n- `openDrawer()`: Displays step configuration details\n- `deleteAllContainers()`: Bulk delete containers via DELETE API\n\n---\n\n### Project Runs Page\n\n**Route:** `GET /projects/{name}/runs` (line 148)  \n**Handler:** `handleProjectRuns()` (lines 336-342)\n\n**Handler Logic:**\n- Resolves project directory by name\n- Calls `renderRunsList()` with project filter\n\n**renderRunsList()** (lines 274-333):\n- Filters runs by project directory\n- Counts retained containers per project\n- Groups runs by task ID\n- Fetches task titles from task provider\n- Returns grouped and sorted runs\n\n**Template:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/runs.html`\n\n**Key Sections:**\n1. **Project Filter** (lines 4-15): Dropdown to filter by project, cleanup button\n2. **Runs Table** (lines 17-54): Displays grouped runs with columns:\n   - Run ID (link to /runs/{id})\n   - Title\n   - Project\n   - Workflow\n   - Type (host/container)\n   - State (badge)\n   - Timing\n   - Container ID\n   - Error message\n3. **Task Grouping**: Runs grouped with task headers showing task ID, title, and status\n\n**API Endpoints Used:**\n- `GET /api/projects/{label}/runs` - Fetch project runs (line 99 in script)\n- `GET /api/containers` DELETE - Clean up containers (line 80)\n\n**JavaScript Features:**\n- `filterByProject()`: Navigate to `/projects/{label}/runs` when project selected\n- `cleanupContainers()`: Delete old containers via DELETE API\n- `poll()`: Polls for run updates every 3 seconds\n- Dynamic row building with task headers and parent/child run relationships\n\n---\n\n### Navigation & Backlinks\n\n**From Project Detail Page:**\n- \"View all runs\" button (line 8) → `/projects/{label}/runs`\n- Breadcrumb \"Projects\" (line 2) → `/`\n- Run dots (line 6) → `/runs/{id}`\n\n**From Project Runs Page:**\n- \"All projects\" filter option → `/`\n- Run ID links → `/runs/{id}`\n- Parent run links (in run detail) → `/runs/{parent-id}`\n\n---\n\n### API Handlers for Project Data\n\n**GET /api/projects/{name}/info** (lines 1235-1326):\n- Docker image from Dockerfile\n- Version number\n- Prompt files with git history\n\n**GET /api/projects/{name}/workflows** (lines 1359-1477):\n- Container workflows (*.cloche files)\n- Host workflows (host.cloche)\n- Step definitions with types, results, config\n- Wire connections\n\n**GET /api/projects/{name}/tasks** (lines 1580-1599):\n- Task pipeline state from orchestration loop\n- Task ID, status, title, assigned state\n\n**GET /api/projects/{name}/runs** (lines 668-674):\n- Grouped runs for project\n- Delegates to renderAPIRuns with project filter\n\n---\n\n### File Paths Summary\n\nAll file paths are absolute:\n\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (1,853 lines)\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html` (535 lines)\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/runs.html` (160 lines)\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/layout.html` (21 lines)\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html` (356 lines)\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/projects.html` (39 lines)\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css`"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: aea9f933de0e12524 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 61561\ntool_uses: 28\nduration_ms: 43998</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"76c13eb5-158e-4526-8203-d3ea7f49bab0","uuid":"8dddb980-ae8c-45f2-946d-48b79e449357","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to find the code related to the \"Project Runs page\" and \"Project page\" in this Go project. This is a CLI/web application called Cloche. Look for:\n\n1. Any web UI templates or handlers related to project runs and project pages\n2. Any HTML templates that render project-related pages\n3. Route definitions for project pages\n\nSearch thoroughly in /workspace for:\n- HTML templates (*.html, *.tmpl, *.gohtml)\n- Web handlers or route definitions mentioning \"project\" and \"runs\"\n- Any existing backlinks or navigation patterns in the UI\n\nReport the full file paths and relevant code snippets.","agentId":"aea9f933de0e12524","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now let me create a comprehensive summary of my findings:\n\n## Summary\n\nI've thoroughly analyzed the Cloche web UI codebase and found all the relevant code related to the \"Project Runs page\" and \"Project Detail page\". Here are the complete findings:\n\n### Web UI File Structure\n\n**Template Files:**\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/layout.html` - Base layout template (533 bytes)\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/projects.html` - Projects listing page (1,297 bytes)\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/runs.html` - Runs listing page (6,585 bytes)\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html` - Run detail page (15,762 bytes)\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html` - **PROJECT DETAIL PAGE** (22,579 bytes)\n\n**Handler & Route Definitions:**\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` - Main handler with all routes (1,853 lines)\n\n**Styling:**\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css` - CSS styling (13,670 bytes)\n\n---\n\n### Route Definitions\n\nThe following routes are defined in `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (lines 147-167):\n\n**HTML Routes:**\n```\nGET /                           → handleProjectOverview    (Projects landing page)\nGET /projects/{name}/runs       → handleProjectRuns        (Project runs page)\nGET /runs                       → handleRunsList           (All runs listing)\nGET /runs/{id}                  → handleRunDetail          (Run detail page)\nGET /projects/{name}            → handleProjectDetail      (Project detail page) ← PROJECT PAGE\nGET /static/*                   → File server\n```\n\n**API Routes:**\n```\nGET /api/projects               → handleAPIProjects\nGET /api/projects/{name}/runs   → handleAPIProjectRuns   (Project runs list API)\nGET /api/runs                   → handleAPIRuns\nGET /api/runs/{id}              → handleAPIRunDetail\nGET /api/runs/{id}/steps/{step}/output → handleAPIStepOutput\nGET /api/runs/{id}/stream       → handleAPIStream        (SSE log streaming)\nPOST /api/runs/{id}/stop        → handleAPIStopRun\nDELETE /api/runs/{id}/container → handleAPIDeleteContainer\nDELETE /api/projects/{name}/containers → handleAPIDeleteProjectContainers\nDELETE /api/containers          → handleAPIDeleteAllContainers\nGET /api/projects/{name}/info   → handleAPIProjectInfo\nGET /api/projects/{name}/info/prompt-diff → handleAPIPromptDiff\nGET /api/projects/{name}/workflows → handleAPIWorkflows\nGET /api/projects/{name}/workflows/{workflow}/steps/{step}/content → handleAPIStepContent\nGET /api/projects/{name}/tasks  → handleAPITasks\n```\n\n---\n\n### Project Detail Page (Project Page)\n\n**Route:** `GET /projects/{name}` (line 151)  \n**Handler:** `handleProjectDetail()` (lines 1199-1233)\n\n**Handler Logic:**\n- Resolves project directory by name/label\n- Lists runs for the project\n- Counts containers for the project\n- Passes data to template: Label, Dir, RecentRuns (dots), ContainerCount\n\n**Template:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html`\n\n**Key Sections in Template:**\n1. **Header** (lines 2): Breadcrumb navigation with project label\n2. **Run History** (lines 4-12): Display recent run status dots with \"View all runs\" button\n3. **Panel 1: Project Info** (lines 14-18): Loads via `/api/projects/{name}/info`\n   - Docker image, version, prompt files with history\n4. **Panel 2: Tasks** (lines 20-24): Loads via `/api/projects/{name}/tasks`\n   - Task pipeline state table\n5. **Panel 3: Workflow View** (lines 26-34): Loads via `/api/projects/{name}/workflows`\n   - Location tabs (Container/Host)\n   - Workflow tabs\n   - DAG visualization with SVG\n6. **Step Drawer** (lines 36-43): Modal for step details\n\n**JavaScript Features:**\n- `loadProjectInfo()`: Fetches project metadata (Docker image, version, prompt files)\n- `toggleDiff()`: Shows/hides git diffs for prompt files\n- `loadWorkflows()`: Builds workflow DAG with step connections\n- `switchLocation()`: Toggles between container and host workflows\n- `showWorkflow()`: Renders Sugiyama-style layout algorithm for graph visualization\n- `openDrawer()`: Displays step configuration details\n- `deleteAllContainers()`: Bulk delete containers via DELETE API\n\n---\n\n### Project Runs Page\n\n**Route:** `GET /projects/{name}/runs` (line 148)  \n**Handler:** `handleProjectRuns()` (lines 336-342)\n\n**Handler Logic:**\n- Resolves project directory by name\n- Calls `renderRunsList()` with project filter\n\n**renderRunsList()** (lines 274-333):\n- Filters runs by project directory\n- Counts retained containers per project\n- Groups runs by task ID\n- Fetches task titles from task provider\n- Returns grouped and sorted runs\n\n**Template:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/runs.html`\n\n**Key Sections:**\n1. **Project Filter** (lines 4-15): Dropdown to filter by project, cleanup button\n2. **Runs Table** (lines 17-54): Displays grouped runs with columns:\n   - Run ID (link to /runs/{id})\n   - Title\n   - Project\n   - Workflow\n   - Type (host/container)\n   - State (badge)\n   - Timing\n   - Container ID\n   - Error message\n3. **Task Grouping**: Runs grouped with task headers showing task ID, title, and status\n\n**API Endpoints Used:**\n- `GET /api/projects/{label}/runs` - Fetch project runs (line 99 in script)\n- `GET /api/containers` DELETE - Clean up containers (line 80)\n\n**JavaScript Features:**\n- `filterByProject()`: Navigate to `/projects/{label}/runs` when project selected\n- `cleanupContainers()`: Delete old containers via DELETE API\n- `poll()`: Polls for run updates every 3 seconds\n- Dynamic row building with task headers and parent/child run relationships\n\n---\n\n### Navigation & Backlinks\n\n**From Project Detail Page:**\n- \"View all runs\" button (line 8) → `/projects/{label}/runs`\n- Breadcrumb \"Projects\" (line 2) → `/`\n- Run dots (line 6) → `/runs/{id}`\n\n**From Project Runs Page:**\n- \"All projects\" filter option → `/`\n- Run ID links → `/runs/{id}`\n- Parent run links (in run detail) → `/runs/{parent-id}`\n\n---\n\n### API Handlers for Project Data\n\n**GET /api/projects/{name}/info** (lines 1235-1326):\n- Docker image from Dockerfile\n- Version number\n- Prompt files with git history\n\n**GET /api/projects/{name}/workflows** (lines 1359-1477):\n- Container workflows (*.cloche files)\n- Host workflows (host.cloche)\n- Step definitions with types, results, config\n- Wire connections\n\n**GET /api/projects/{name}/tasks** (lines 1580-1599):\n- Task pipeline state from orchestration loop\n- Task ID, status, title, assigned state\n\n**GET /api/projects/{name}/runs** (lines 668-674):\n- Grouped runs for project\n- Delegates to renderAPIRuns with project filter\n\n---\n\n### File Paths Summary\n\nAll file paths are absolute:\n\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (1,853 lines)\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html` (535 lines)\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/runs.html` (160 lines)\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/layout.html` (21 lines)\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html` (356 lines)\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/projects.html` (39 lines)\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css`"}],"totalDurationMs":43998,"totalTokens":61561,"totalToolUseCount":28,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":871,"cache_read_input_tokens":58640,"output_tok